---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About - Jordi's Blog">
  <div class="bg-white py-16 sm:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <h1>About Jordi's Blog</h1>
        
        <p class="lead">
          Welcome to my financial analysis blog, where I dive deep into precious metals markets, 
          investment strategies, and market manipulation research.
        </p>

        <h2>About the Author</h2>
        <p>
          I'm Jordi Posthumus, a financial analyst specializing in precious metals research. 
          My work focuses on comprehensive market analysis, combining quantitative data with 
          fundamental research to identify investment opportunities and understand market dynamics.
        </p>

        <h2>Research Focus Areas</h2>
        
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
          <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Precious Metals Analysis</h3>
            <p class="text-blue-800">
              In-depth research on gold and silver markets, supply-demand dynamics, 
              industrial applications, and price forecasts.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-green-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-green-900 mb-2">Market Manipulation Research</h3>
            <p class="text-green-800">
              Investigation into paper market manipulation, COMEX operations, 
              and the divergence between physical and futures markets.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-purple-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-purple-900 mb-2">Industrial Demand Analysis</h3>
            <p class="text-purple-800">
              Research on emerging technologies driving precious metals demand: 
              solar panels, electric vehicles, AI infrastructure.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-orange-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-orange-900 mb-2">Investment Strategy</h3>
            <p class="text-orange-800">
              Practical investment insights, risk management strategies, 
              and portfolio allocation recommendations for precious metals.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2>Latest Analysis</h2>
        
        <article class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3>The Great Silver Squeeze: 338% Gain in 2025</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Comprehensive analysis revealing how silver shattered the $60 barrier for the first time in history, 
            driven by structural supply deficits and COMEX inventory crises.
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded border mb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Key Findings:</h4>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
              <li>Fifth consecutive year of supply deficits (820M oz total)</li>
              <li>Record industrial demand led by solar and electric vehicles</li>
              <li>COMEX registered silver inventory draining at unprecedented rates</li>
              <li>Physical premiums 15-25% above paper prices globally</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
            Analysis Date: December 10, 2025 | Current Silver Price: $61.69/oz
          </p>
        </article>

        <h2>Contact & Collaboration</h2>
        
        <p>
          I'm always interested in discussing market analysis, investment research, and collaboration opportunities. 
          If you're working on similar research or have questions about precious metals markets, feel free to reach out.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg mt-8">
          <h3>Important Disclaimer</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800">
            All analysis published on this blog is for educational and research purposes only. 
            This does not constitute financial advice. Please conduct your own due diligence 
            before making any investment decisions and consult with a qualified financial advisor.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
